title: Twenty Thousand Leagues Under the Sea
creator: Jules Verne
description: LibriVox recording of Twenty Thousand Leagues Under the Sea, by Jules Verne. Captain Nemo, The Nautilus, and the mysterious depths of the ocean. Unforgettable. Come join an adventure that will roam among coral and pearls, sharks and giant squid, with wonders of biology and engineering that will thrust us from the Antarctic to Atlantis. Whether voyaging a yarn of the glorious unknown, a tale of the darkness that grips the heart of men, or a reinterpretation of Homer's Odyssey, we'll all enjoy the fantastic trip. Seasickness optional. (Summary by Marlodianne) For further information, including links to M4B audio book, online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.
subject: librivox; audiobook; literature
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: I am sorry to have to say that I couln't even manage to listen to it. I startet playing the first chapter, and I am sorry to whoever read it, I'm not trying to be mean, but I started laughing. I'm sorry, but it was not any good.
This is such a great story even after reading/hearing it so many times. The reader does a fantastic job with it.
